<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>On Show: Gallery and Museum Exhibits and Shows</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>DETROIT</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   The Detroit Institute of Arts:
   ``Furniture by Wendell Castle,'' first exhibit of
non-traditional furniture designed by the American artist. Through
Feb. 5.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>PHILADELPHIA</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   Dolan-Maxwell:
   Frank Stella, ``The Waves.'' Through Jan. 28.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>PARAMUS, N.J.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   Bergen Museum of Art and Science:
   Work of Greg Wyatt, fantasy-realist sculptor. Jan. 18-March 25.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>WASHINGTON</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
   National Museum of American Art, Smithsonian Institution:
   
   ``Training the Hand and Eye: American Drawings From the
Cooper-Hewitt Museum.'' Through Feb. 3.
   
   National Museum of African Art:
   ``Icons: Ideals and Power in the Art of Africa.'' Through Sept.
3.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>STAMFORD, Conn.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   
